<reggrp_short_dscr>:
Frame statistics
------------------------------
<reggrp_public_text>:
Address space for reading counters for port number or service index specified in
XQS:SYSTEM:STAT_CFG.STAT_VIEW.

I.e. once a given port number or service index is written to STAT_VIEW, then the counters
of that port/service can be accesses through the XQS:STAT address space.

Only a subset of the 1024 addresses in XQS:STAT are used.

The 10 bit address for XQS:STAT is calculated as follows:

Rx forward counters:
  Packet counter address:   0       + <color>*8 + <priority>

Rx port drop counters:
  Packet counter address:   16       + <color>*8 + <priority>

Rx local drop counter:
  Packet counter address: 32

Tx port transmit counters:
  Packet counter address:   256       + <color>*8 + <priority>

Tx port abort counter:
  Packet counter address:   272      

Ingress service drop counters:
  Packet counter address:   512       + <color>    

Egress service Tx counter:
  Packet counter address:   768       + <color>    

<color>:
0b0: Green (DP mapped through QSYS:SYSTEM:DP_MAP.DP)
0b1: Yellow (DP mapped through QSYS:SYSTEM:DP_MAP.DP)

For all the above statistics counters, here is a corresponding octet counter available at the address added 64 (32 LSBs) and 128 (8 MSBs).

When LS byte counter is read, the value for MS byte counter is latched, i.e. LS byte must be read before MS byte is read.

Counters for a given port number or service index can be cleared using XQS:SYSTEM:STAT_CFG.STAT_CLEAR_SHOT.
